    The latest version of the Angular CLI no longer includes the FormsModule within app.module.ts by default for new projects. So you need to check your app.module.ts file. If you are using the very latest Angular CLI you won't have these lines.

    import { FormsModule } from '@angular/forms';

    @NgModule({
      imports: [
        FormsModule

    Manually add the FormsModule if you don't have it. If you do have it, remember to update your Angular CLI for the next project.

  • Setup overview - Git setup, ng new QuickChat --routing, Firebase console to make a yourusername-quick-chat project, check in your starting code via VCS, add the FormsModule to app.module.ts, add Firebase via AngularFire2, add Angular Material 2 with any color theme you like (link to the MaterialModule gist), add Angular Flex Layout, add an md-toolbar, fix the .favicon, put a space in the title, add a margin 0 body rule to styles.scss and a background color of #ddd, finally modify .angular-cli.json to default to scss and set defaults to not make spec files. Easy. :)
